WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
Why this post matters

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
An evidence-backed intervention design for measurable behavior change in high-change sounds strategic, but the real gap is execution quality under pressure.

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Use a compact loop: signal, decision, action, and evidence review each week.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Define baseline first, run one experiment, and inspect deltas before scaling.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
Teams get faster follow-through because decisions and reinforcement happen in the same cadence.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
If a step does not move outcomes after two cycles, remove it and simplify.
